<head>
<Title> Status of OMB Policies</Title>
</head>

<body background="/tpg/gif/tpgpattern.gif"> 
<center><IMG SRC="/tpg/fed_gts/cope/copehead.gif" alt="Resource Guide to Federal Program Compliance Audits"></center><P>

<h2> Status of OMB Policies</h2>

<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT>OMB Circular A-133, <I>Audits of Institutions of Higher Education
and Other Non-Profit Institutions</I></H3>

<P>
OMB has proposed revisions to Circular A-133 that would bring state and local governments under the circular, permit biennial audits in certain circumstances and address the allowability of audit costs for subrecipients. The proposal was published in the Nov. 5, 1996, <i>Federal Register</i>, and comments are due to OMB by Jan. 6, 1997. OMB plans to rescind Circular A-128, <i>Audits of State and
Local Governments</i>, when the proposal is finalized. These changes would fully implement the Single Audit Act Amendments of 1996 (P.L. 104-156), which applies to audits of fiscal years ending after June 30, 1996. Many of the new statutory requirements had already been incorporated into Circular A-133 when OMB revised it in April 1996. <A HREF="/tpg/fed_gts/cope/cope_a133.html">Click here to retrieve the proposal.</A></P>


<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT>OMB Compliance Supplement</H3>
</P>

<P>
OMB plans to issue an initial draft of an updated compliance supplement that is used by auditors performing single audits and other financial and compliance audits of federal assistance recipients. The new compliance supplement will incorporate provisions of the Single Audit Act Amendments of 1996, as well as OMB Circular A-133. As the revision progresses, up-to-date information on the status of the proposal will be provided here by the editors of the <I>Resource Guide to Federal Program Compliance Audits</I>.
</P>


