<center><IMG SRC="/tpg/fed_gts/gran/granhead.gif" alt="Federal Grants Management
Handbook"></center><P>

<h2> Status of OMB Policies</h2>

<H3 ALIGN=LEFT>OMB Circular A-133, <I>Audits of Institutions of Higher Education
and Other Non-Profit Institutions</I></H3>

<P>
OMB has proposed revisions to Circular A-133 that would bring state and local governments under the circular, permit biennial audits in certain circumstances and address the allowability of audit costs for subrecipients. The proposal was published in the Nov. 5, 1996, <i>Federal Register</i>, and comments are due to OMB by Jan. 6, 1997. OMB plans to rescind Circular A-128, <i>Audits of State and
Local Governments</i>, when the proposal is finalized. These changes would fully implement the Single Audit Act Amendments of 1996 (P.L. 104-156), which applies to audits of fiscal years ending after June 30, 1996. Many of the new statutory requirements had already been incorporated into Circular A-133 when OMB revised it in April 1996. The <i>Federal Grants Management Handbook</i> provides complete analyses of OMB circulars and proposals related to grants management. <A HREF="/tpg/fed_gts/gran/gran_a133.html">Click here to retrieve the proposal.</A></P>



