<html>
<head>
<Title>UST Resources on the Internet</Title>
</head>

<body background="/tpg/gif/tpgpattern.gif">
<IMG SRC = "/tpg/enviro/ustt/ustthead.gif" alt="Underground Storage Tank Guide"><P>


<h2>UST Resources on the Internet</h2><P>

The Internet can help UST owners comply with federal regulations and answer questions about products, consultants, standards, organizations, fire codes and the petroleum industry.

This resource guide contains sections on: 

<UL>
	<LI><A HREF="#legislative">Legislative and Regulatory Information</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#state">State Agencies</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#third-party">Third-party Testing and Standards Organizations</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#trade">Trade Associations</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#newsgroups">Newsgroups</A>
	<LI><A HREF="#publications">Online Publications</A>
</UL>


<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT><A NAME="legislative">Legislative and Regulatory Information</A></H3>
</P>

<P>
U.S. Environmental Protection Agency's (EPA) web page: <A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/epaoswer/ust.htm">http://www.epa.gov/epaoswer/ust.htm</A>
</P>

<P>
EPA's RCRA, CERCLA and EPCRA Hotline: <A HREF="http://www.epa.gov/epaoswer/hotline/index.htm">http://www.epa.gov/epaoswer/hotline/index.htm</A>
</P>

<P>
EPA's Technology Transfer Network (TTN) is managed by EPA's Office of Air Quality Planning and Standards and provides information on the Clean Air Act (accessed through drive E): <A HREF="ftp://ttnftp.rtpnc.epa.gov">ftp://ttnftp.rtpnc.epa.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
EPA's Clu-In site provides information to the hazardous waste remediation community about innovative treatment technologies, and allows users to telnet directly to the Clu-In bulletin board system: <A HREF="http://clu-in.com">http://clu-in.com</A>
</P>


<P>
<I>Federal Register</I> Online: <A HREF="http://www.access.gpo.gov">http://www.access.gpo.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
U.S. House of Representatives: <A HREF="http://www.house.gov">http://www.house.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
Thomas, a site created by the 104th Congress to provide free federal legislative information: <A HREF="http://thomas.loc.gov">http://thomas.loc.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
U.S. Internal Revenue Service: <A HREF="http://www.irs.ustreas.gov">http://www.irs.ustreas.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
U.S. Occupational Safety and Health Administration: <A HREF="http://www.osha.gov">http://www.osha.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
U.S. Senate: <A HREF="http://www.senate.gov">http://www.senate.gov</A>
</P>

<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT><A NAME="state">State Agencies</A></H3>
</P>

<P>
Florida Department of Environmental Protection has information on state tank bills, the petroleum cleanup participation program and the state's soil cleanup goals on its web site: <A HREF="http://www.dep.state.fl.us/waste/programs.htm">http://www.dep.state.fl.us/waste/programs.htm</A>
</P>

<P>
Pennsylvania Department of Environmental Protection: <A HREF="http://www.dep.state.pa.us">http://www.dep.state.pa.us</A>
</P>

<P>
The Texas Natural Resources Conservation Commission (TNRCC) site contains petroleum UST registration information, Stage II vapor recovery requirements and information on the petroleum storage tank remediation fund: <A HREF="http://www.tnrcc.state.tx.us/waste/pst/index.html">http://www.tnrcc.state.tx.us/waste/pst/index.html</A>
</P>

<P>
<A NAME="third-party"><H3 ALIGN=LEFT>Third-party Testing and Standards Organizations</H3></A>
</P>

<P>
Organizations that independently test petroleum equipment to ensure that it meets applicable industry standards and organizations that publish standards for petroleum equipment or fire codes also have posted useful information on the Web.
</P>

<P>
American National Standards Institute: <A HREF="http://www.ansi.org">http://www.ansi.org</A>
</P>

<P>
American Petroleum Institute: <A HREF="http://www.api.org">http://www.api.org</A>
</P>

<P>
American Society of Testing and Materials: <A HREF="http://www.astm.org">http://www.astm.org</A>
</P>

<P>
Factory Mutual: <A HREF="http://www.factorymutual.com">http://www.factorymutual.com</A>
</P>

<P>
International Conference of Building Officials: <A HREF="http://www.icbo.org">http://www.icbo.org</A>
</P>

<P>
Ken Wilcox Associates Inc.: <A HREF="http://www.kwaleak.com">http://www.kwaleak.com</A>
</P>

<P>
National Fire Protection Association: <A HREF="http://www.wpi.edu/%7Efpe/nfpa.html">http://www.wpi.edu/~fpe/nfpa.html</A>
</P>

<P>
Steel Tank Institute (STI): <A HREF="http://www.steeltank.com">http://www.steeltank.com</A>
</P>

<P>
Underwriters Laboratories Inc.: <A HREF="http://www.ul.com">http://www.ul.com</A>
</P>

<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT><A NAME="trade">Trade Associations</A></H3>
</P>

<P>
The American Society of Petroleum Operations Engineers (ASPOE) has a site providing information on the group, its members, its publications and special events: <A HREF="http://www.bizinfonet.com/assn/aspoe.htm">http://www.bizinfonet.com/assn/aspoe.htm</A>
</P>

<P>
The Petroleum Marketers Association of America (PMAA) has a site that contains information about PMAA, its activities and links to other petroleum-related web sites: <A HREF="http://www.pmaa.org">http://www.pmaa.org</A>
</P>

<P>
The site for the Society of Petroleum Engineers (SPE) provides information on the group, its members, its publications and special events: <A HREF="http://www.spe.org">http://www.spe.org</A>
</P>

<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT><A NAME="newsgroups">Newsgroups</A></H3>
</P>

<P>
Web surfers also can check out different newsgroup or "chat" sessions online. Sessions are similar to bulletin boards and allow individuals to post questions on a particular topic to the chat group. Typically, when posting a question, the person leaves an e-mail address to which others perusing the bulletin board can reply to if they have an appropriate answer. 
</P>

<P>
One newsgroup of particular interest for the petroleum industry is the Petroleum USENET group which is located at <A HREF="news:sci.geo.petroleum">news:sci.geo.petroleum</A>
</P>

<P>
<H3 ALIGN=LEFT><A NAME="publications">Online Publications</A></H3>
</P>

<P>
Issues of <I>The Journal of Petroleum Marketing (JPM)</I>, which is published by PMAA, can be found at <A HREF="http://www.jpetromark.com">http://www.jpetromark.com</A>
</P>

<P>
<I>Soil &amp; Groundwater Cleanup</I>'s site contains magazine articles, product information and industry contacts for the soil and groundwater cleanup industry: <A HREF="http://www.gvi.net/soils">http://www.gvi.net/soils</A>
</P>



<center>
