<center><h1>Styles</h1></center>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>

These style templates are intended as guidelines for the various
documents listed below.  While their use will enhance uniformity of
the entire WWW network, suggestions are encouraged to improve and
upgrade their formats.  They can be viewed then saved, or saved
directly depending on the capabilities of the browser.  The list of
file types will grow as the ANS-WG develops.

<dl>
  <dt> <a href="basic.html">Basic File</a>
  <dd> This is the basic format of all The ANSWER's files.  The
       following formats will, for the most part, also include this
       style.
       <p>

  <dt> Book Reviews
  <dd> These styles are used to create the book reviews, as
       recommended by the Electronic Communications and Publications
       Special Committee.  The purpose of book reviews is to make
       legacy information available on-line without jeopardizing its
       copyright and without converting huge amounts of data.
       <ul>
	 <li> <a href="reviews/issue.html">Journal/Magazine Issue
	      Review</a>
	      <i><a href="reviews/issue.eg.html">(example)</a></i>
	 <li> <a href="reviews/article.html">Journal/Magazine Article Review</a>
	      <i><a href="reviews/article.eg.html">(example)</a></i>
       </ul>
