<html> <head>
<title>ANS Topical Meeting: Low-Level Radiation Health Effects</title>
</head>

<body background=/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif>
<center>
<table width=600><tr><td>
<center>
<h3>ANS TOPICAL MEETING</h3>
<h1>Low-Level Radiation Health Effects</h1>
</center>
<p>
<a name="monpm"><img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif></a>
<p>
<center><h3>Monday, November 11</h3></center>
<dl>
  <dt> <i>1:00 p.m.</i>
  <dd> 
       <dl>
	 <dt> <i><b>Biological Research Confirming Beneficial Effects</b></i><br>
	      sponsored by BMD; cosponsored by PD.<br>
	      Session organizer: Charles C. Thomas, Jr. (NTC).<br>
	      All invited	
	 <dd> 
	      <ul>
		<li> Research Status on Radiation Hormesis at CRIEPI,
		     Sadao Hattori (CRIEPI-Japan)
		<li> Fundamental and Clinical Studies on Tumor Control
		     by TBI, Kiyohiko Sakamoto (Tohoku Univ-Japan),
		     Miyako Myojin (Sapporo Natl Hosp-Japan)
		<li> Influence of Low Doses of X Rays on
		     Radiation-Induced Genetic Instability, Masami
		     Watanabe, Seiji Kodama, Keiji Suzuki (Nagasaki
		     Univ-Japan)
		<li> Antistress Effect of Low-Level Radiation, Takeshi
		     Yamada, Yukihisa Miyachi (Toho Univ SM-Japan),
		     Harumi Ohyama (NIRS-Japan)
		<li> Alternative Model to the Current
		     DNA-Damage-Mutation Model in Radiation
		     Carcinogenesis, Tsutomu Sugahara (HRF-Japan)
		<li> Health Benefits from Low-Dose Irradiation,
		     T. D. Luckey (Luckey Consult)
	      </ul>

       </dl>
</dl>
<p>
<a name="tuesam"><img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif></a>
<p>

<center><h3>Tuesday, November 12</h3></center>

<dl>
  <dt> <i>8:30 a.m.</i>
  <dd> 
       <dl>
	 <dt> <i><b>Biological and Epidemiological Data and the LNT Model</b></i><br>
	      sponsored by BMD; cosponsored by PD.<br>
	      Session organizer: Charles C. Thomas, Jr. (NTC)	
	 <dd> 
	      <ul>
		<li> The Linear, No-Threshold Hypothesis Linking
		     Health Effects to Tissue Absorbed Dose Appears
		     Principally Inapplicable at Low Doses, Ludwig
		     E. Feinendegen (DOE, Germantown), Victor P. Bond
		     (BNL), Charles A. Sondhaus (Univ of Arizona),
		     invited
		<li> The Nuclear Shipyard Worker Study Eight Years
		     Later, John Cameron (Cameron Consult), invited
		<li> Radiation and Risk-A Look at the Data, Mario
		     E. Schillaci (LANL), invited
		<li> Complementary Sigmoid and Linear Functions and
		     Their Impact on the Radiation LNH,
		     L. Wielopolski, V. Bond (BNL), invited
		<li> Use of Nonlinear Dose-Effect Models to Predict
		     Consequences, Fritz A. Seller (IRS), Joseph
		     L. Alvarez (Auxier &amp; Assoc), invted
		<li> Nonlinear Dose Response Model with Repair and
		     Repair Suppression, Bobby E. Leonard (Int Acad
		     Hi-Tech Svc)
	      </ul>
       </dl>
       <a name="tuespm"><p></a>

  <dt> <i>1:00 p.m.</i>
  <dd> 
       <dl>
	 <dt> <i><b>Human Data from Radium and Radon Exposures</b></i><br>
	      sponsored by BMD; cosponsored by PD.<br>
	      Session organizers: Charles C. Thomas, Jr. (NTC), James Muckerheide (Comm Mass).<br>
	      All invited	
	 <dd> 
	      <ul>
		<li> Problems in the Radon versus Lung Cancer Test of
		     the Linear No-Threshold Theory and a Procedure
		     for Resolving Them, Bernard L. Cohen (Univ of
		     Pittsburgh)
		<li> Radon in Europe, Klaus Becker (DIN-Germany)
		<li> Indoor Radon and Lung Cancer in Radium-Dial
		     Workers, John S. Neuberger (Univ of Kansas MS),
		     John Rundo (Rundo, ret.)
		<li> Some Scientific Landmarks of the MIT Radium
		     Toxicity Studies, Constantine J. Maletskos
		     (Maletskos Consult)
		<li> Recent History of the Human Radium Exposure
		     Study: The DOE Phaseout, Robert G. Thomas
		     (R. Thomas Consult)
	      </ul>
       </dl>
</dl>
<p>
<a name="wedam"><img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif></a>
<p>

<center><h3>Wednesday, November 13</h3></center>

<dl>
  <dt> <i>8:30 a.m.</i>
  <dd> 
       <dl>
	 <dt> <i><b>Applying Science and Data to Setting Standards</b></i><br>
	      sponsored by BMD; cosponsored by PD.<br>
	      Session organizers: Charles C. Thomas, Jr. (NTC), James Muckerheide (Comm Mass).<br>
	      All invited	
	 <dd> 
	      <ul>
		<li> Collective Dose: Dogma, Tool, or Trauma? Klaus
		     Becker (DIN-Germany)
		<li> Has Radiation Protection Become a Health Hazard?
		     Theodore Rockwell (MPR Assoc)
		<li> Comparative Assessment of Standards Development
		     for Radiation and Other Hazardous Exposures,
		     Jerry J. Cohen (Cohen, ret.), Ronald L. Kathren
		     (Washington State Univ), Craig F. Smith
		     (Booz.Allen &amp; Hamilton)
		<li> Sources of Confusion in Establishment of
		     Radiation Exposure Guidelines, Robert G. Thomas
		     (R. Thomas Consult)
		<li> Equivalent Dose and Effective Dose Are
		     Scientifically Unsatisfactory Quantities, John
		     Cameron (Cameron Consult)
		<li> The Effects of Low Doses of Ionizing
		     Radiation-A Question of Ethics,
		     A. N. Tschaeche (Tschaeche Consult)
	      </ul>
       </dl>
       <a name="wedpm"><p></a>

  <dt> <i>1:00 p.m.</i>
  <dd> 
       <dl>
	 <dt> <i><b>Research Work and Policy Initiatives Needed to Effect Change-Panel</b></i><br>
	      sponsored by BMD; cosponsored by PD.<br>
	      Session organizer: Charles C. Thomas, Jr. (NTC)	
