<html> <head>
<title>ANS Professional Development Workshop: Preventive Maintenance and Condition Monitoring</title>
</head>

<body background=/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif>
<center>
<table width=600><tr><td>
<center>
<h3>ANS PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT WORKSHOP</h3>
<h1>Preventive Maintenance and Condition Monitoring</h1>
<table width=100%>
<tr align=center>
  <td>Sunday, November 10, 1996</td>
  <td>8:30 a.m.-4:30 p.m.</td>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
<p>
<center>
Workshop Organizer:<p>
Carolyn Heising, Iowa State University
</center>
<p>

Registration for this workshop is $325 for ANS members, $375
for nonmembers.  Registration includes copies of workshop
handouts and materials and morning and afternoon coffee breaks.
<p>

This workshop will introduce attendees to the NRC maintenance
rule that is effective July 1, 1996, and ways to introduce
continuous process improvement through predictive maintenance
and condition monitoring.  Examples applied to reactor coolant
pumps and diesel generators will be provided by instructors.
<p>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
<p>

Workshop Outline
<table width=100% border=5 cellpadding=5><tr>
      </ul>
  <td>8:30 a.m.</td>
  <td><i><b>Introductory Remarks</b></i><br>
      Dr. Carolyn Heising, Professor of Industrial and Nuclear Engineering, Iowa State University
</tr><tr>

   <td>9:00 a.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>"The Maintenance Rule and continuous Improvement of
      Nuclear Plants,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Steven Arndt, Technical Advisor, USNRC
      Technical Training Center, Tennessee</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>10:00 am</td>
   <td><i><b>"On-Line Condition Monitoring:  Diesel Generator
      Application,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Hash Hashemian, AMS Corporation</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>11:00 a.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>"Process Control in the Nuclear Industry:  Reactor
      Coolant Pump Application,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Carolyn Heising, Iowa State University</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>12 Noon</td>
   <td><i><b>Lunch Break</b></i></td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>1:00 p.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>"Neural Networks in Process Diagnostics,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Wes Hines, Research Assistant Professor, University of Tennessee</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>2:00 p.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>"SPDS Technology:  A Look to the Future,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Madeline Feltus, Assistant Professor, Pennsylvania State University</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>3:00 p.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>"Japanese Experience in Predictive Maintenance,
      Condition Monitoring, and Neural Networks,"</b></i><br>
      Dr. Masaharu Kitarura and Dr. Robert Kozma, Professors of Nuclear Engineering,
      University of Tohoku, Japan</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>4:00 p.m.</td>
   <td><i><b>Closing Remarks,</b></i><br>
      Dr. Carolyn Heising, Iowa State University</td>
</tr><tr>

   <td>4:30 p.m.</td>
   <td>Workshop adjourns</td>
</table>
</table>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
