<html> <head>
<title>ANS Professional Development Workshop: Criticality Accident Analysis</title>
</head>

<body background=/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif>
<center>
<table width=600><tr><td>
<center>
<h3>ANS PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT WORKSHOP</h3>
<h1>Criticality Accident Analysis</h1>
<table width=100%>
<tr align=center>
  <td>Thursday, November 14</td>
  <td>8 a.m.-4:30 p.m</td>
</table>
</center>
<p>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
<p>

<center> Worskshop Organizer:<p>
Adolf Garcia, U.S. Department of Energy, Idaho
</center>
<p>

Registration for this workshop is $300 for ANS members, $375 for
nonmembers.  Registration includes copies of workshop handouts
and materials and morning and afternoon coffee breaks.
<p>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
<p>

<center>Workshop Outline:</center>
<ol>
  <li> I.   Criticality Accidents - Introduction
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Statistics--numbers, types, consequences
	 <li> B. Characteristics--power history, energy release,
	      source terms
	 <li> C. Methods and tools for analysis
       </ol>

  <li> II.  Historical Survey
       <ol>
	 <li> A. United States/United Kingdom/France
	 <li> B. Russia
       </ol>

  <li> III. Criticality Analysis - Statics
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Excess reactivity, addition rate
	 <li> B. Temperature coefficients
	 <li> C. Use of Monte Carlo, discrete ordinates codes
       </ol>

  <li> IV.  Excursion Dynamics
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Point-kinetics modeling
	 <li> B. Time-dependent transport analysis
	 <li> C. Energy evolution
       </ol>

  <li> V.   Validatio/Experimental Data
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Solutions (CRAC/SILENE/KEWB)
	 <li> B. Metal systems/Burst reactors
	 <li> C. Critical experiments/Reactors
	 <li> D. Future Directions
       </ol>

  <li> VI.  Technical Consequences
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Source terms
	 <li> B. Confinement Analysis
	 <li> C. Dose-dispersion calculations
       </ol>

  <li> VII. Emergency Planning/Response
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Orders and Standards
	 <li> B. Criticality alarms
	 <li> C. Accident dosimetry
	 <li> D. Medical response planning
       </ol>

  <li> VIII.Course Wrap-up
       <ol>
	 <li> A. Panel discussion
	 <li> B. Questions &amp; answers
       </ol>
</ol>

</table>
<img src=/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif>
<table width=600>
  <tr>
    <td valign=middle><a href="/"><img src="/graphics/gifs/atom.t.gif"
align=left>Return to<br>Home Page</a></td>
    <td align=center><address><a href="/guild">ANS Webweavers' Guild</a>
<a href="mailto:wg-chair@ans.neep.wisc.edu">&lt;wg-chair@ans.neep.wisc.edu&gt;</a></address></td>
  </tr>
</table>

