   <TITLE>ANS Exec. Conference Monday Program</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif">

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="600" >
<TR>
<TD>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>ADVANCE PROGRAM &amp; MEETING REGISTRATION</H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>ANS EXECUTIVE CONFERENCE</H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Decommissioning and Spent Fuel Disposal</I></H3>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Monday, April 28, 1997</H1>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif" HEIGHT=3 WIDTH=600></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>7:00 am - 4:30 pm</H3>

<CENTER><P><B>MEETING REGISTRATION</B></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>8:00 am  12:00 pm</H3>

<CENTER><P>I<B>NTRODUCTORY COMMENTS AND WELCOME TO THE PACIFIC NORTHWEST</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><I>Mr. Richard E. Dyer, Senior Vice President, Marketing and
Power Supply Planning, Portland General Electric Company, Portland, OR</I></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>GENERAL SESSION</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>&quot;Nuclear Power Plant Decommissioning and Spent Fuel
Disposal  The Shifting Paradigm&quot;</I></B></P></CENTER>

<DL>
<DT>Session Chairman &amp; Coordinator:</DT>

<DD><B>Michael B. Lackey</B>, <I>General Manager, Decommissioning and Engineering,
Portland General Electric Company, Trojan Nuclear Power Plant, Rainier,
OR</I></DD>

<DT>Speakers:</DT>

<DL>
<DT><B>Kenneth C. Rogers</B>, <I>Commissioner, U.S. Nuclear Regulatory
Commission, Washington, DC</I></DT>

<DD>Commissioner Rogers will discuss the status of NRC decommissioning
regulations, and the Commission's general and non-project specific views
on current decommissioning and spent fuel management programs. </DD>

<DT><B>Ronald Eachus</B>, <I>Commissioner, Oregon Public Utility Commission,
Portland, OR</I></DT>

<DD>From the perspective of the state regulatory agency, Mr. Eachus will
discuss the issues associated with the early closure of a large nuclear
facility.</DD>

<DT><B>Robert A. Fenech</B>, <I>Vice President, Nuclear Operations, Consumers
Power Company, Jackson, MI </I></DT>

<DD>Mr. Fenech will talk about the corporate level activities associated
with the planned shutdown of an operating nuclear unit, and the spent fuel
management alternatives associated with Consumer's Big Rock Point and Palisades
units.</DD>

<DT><B>A representative from the U.S. Department of Energy</B>, <I>Washington,
DC</I>,</DT>

<DD>will discuss the status and future options related to temporary away-from-reactor
spent fuel storage.</DD>

<DT><B>Andrew C. Kadak</B>, <I>President, Yankee Atomic Electric Company,
Bolton, MA</I> </DT>

<DD>Dr. Kadak will focus his discussion on the Yankee management perspectives
at the Yankee Rowe and Connecticut Yankee plants.</DD>
</DL>
</DL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>12:00 pm - 1:30 pm</H3>

<CENTER><P><B>GROUP LUNCHEON</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>Don W. Miller</B>,<I> President, American Nuclear Society,
Columbus, OH<BR>
</I>Dr. Miller will discuss American Nuclear Society operations and the
need for, and benefits of utility/industry support of ANS programs.</P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>1:30 pm - 5:00 pm </H3>

<CENTER><P><B>AFTERNOON SESSION</B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B><I>&quot;Regulatory Influences and Public Interests&quot;</I></B></P></CENTER>

<DL>
<DT>Session Chairman &amp; Coordinator:</DT>

<DD><B>Thomas D. Ryan,</B> <I>Senior Vice President, Regulatory and Policy
Reform, Nuclear Energy Institute, Washington, DC</I> </DD>

<DT>Speakers:</DT>

<DL>
<DT><B>Thomas D. Ryan</B>, <I>Senior Vice President, Regulatory and Policy
Reform, Nuclear Energy Institute, Washington, DC</I></DT>

<DD>Dr. Ryan will discuss the NEI initiatives related to decommissioning,
long term spent fuel management, GTCC waste, and mixed waste management.</DD>

<DT><B>David Stewart Smith</B>, <I>Administrator, Energy Resource Division,
Oregon Department of Energy, Salem OR </I></DT>

<DD>Mr. Smith will discuss the state of Oregon's perspective on public
participation in the decommissioning regulatory process.</DD>

<DT><B>Ann S. Bisconti</B>, <I>President, Bisconti Research, Inc., Chevy
Chase, MD</I></DT>

<DD>Ms. Bisconti will discuss public perception of the decommissioning
and management of spent fuel at nuclear power facilities. </DD>

<DT>A representative from the <B>U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission</B>,
<I>Washington, DC</I>, </DT>

<DD>will discuss NRC programs and perspectives related to the decommissioning
and long term management of spent fuel. </DD>

<DT>A member of the <B>National Association of Regulatory Utility Commissioners</B>,</DT>

<DD>will discuss the decommissioning and long term spent fuel management
from the states economic and regulatory perspective.</DD>

<DT><B>William J. Manion</B>, <I>President, NES, Inc. Ridgefield, CT </I></DT>

<DD>Mr. Manion will discuss the societal and historical aspects of decommissioning
of nuclear power plants. </DD>
</DL>
</DL>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

