<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>ANS Exec. Conference Tuesday Program</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.01Gold (Win95; I) [Netscape]">
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif">

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="600" >
<TR>
<TD>
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>ADVANCE PROGRAM &amp; MEETING REGISTRATION</H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>ANS EXECUTIVE CONFERENCE</H3>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><I>Decommissioning and Spent Fuel Disposal</I></H3>

<H1 ALIGN=CENTER>Tuesday, April 29, 1997</H1>

<P><IMG SRC="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif" HEIGHT=3 WIDTH=600></P>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>7:00 am </H3>

<CENTER><P><I>Busses will depart from the hotel at 7:00 am and arrive at
the Trojan nuclear power plant at approximately 8:15 am.</I></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>8:30 am -12:00 pm </H3>

<CENTER><P><B>A DAY AT THE TROJAN NUCLEAR POWER PLANT <BR>
<I>&quot;Spent Fuel Disposal Programs and Technology&quot; </I></B></P></CENTER>

<P>This session will present the status of several planned and implemented
dry site spent fuel storage programs. Each set of contributors will discuss
the technology being used for fuel storage at their reactor sites. Presenters
will describe how the site specific factors affected the decisions, non-specific
life cycle costs, and the unknowns that remain. </P>

<DL>
<DT>Session Chairman &amp; Coordinator: </DT>

<DD><B>Daniel C. Gildow</B>, <I>Spent Fuel Management, Portland General
Electric Company, Trojan Nuclear Power Plant, Rainier, OR</I> </DD>

<DT>Speakers: </DT>

<DL>
<DT><I>The Sierra Nuclear TRANSTOR system at the Trojan Nuclear Plant </I></DT>

<DD><B>Daniel C. Gildow</B>, ISFSI Project Manager, Portland General Electric
Company, Trojan Nuclear Power Plant, Rainier, OR, and Art McSherry, Sierra
Nuclear, Scotts Valley, CA </DD>

<DT><I>The NAC system at Yankee Rowe </I></DT>

<DD><B>Russell A. Mellor</B>, Manager of Operation &amp; Decommissioning
Manager, Yankee Atomic Electric Company, Bolton, MA, and Edward M. Davis,
President and Chief Executive Officer, NAC International, Inc., Norcross,
GA </DD>

<DT><I>The NUHOMS system at Rancho Seco</I> </DT>

<DD><B>James Shetler</B>, Deputy Assistant General Manager, Nuclear, Sacramento
Municipal Utilities District, Sacramento, CA, and Vince Franceschi, San
Jose, CA </DD>

<DT><I>The HOLTEC system at Dresden </I></DT>

<DD><B>Charles W. Schroeder</B>, Manager, Decommissioning, Commonwealth
Edison Company, Downers Grove, IL, and Dr. Singh from HOLTEC</DD>

<DT><I>The TN system at a TN user facility </I></DT>

<DD><B>David M. Dawson</B>, Senior Vice President, Transnuclear, Inc.,
Somers, NY, and a representative from a TN user utility. </DD>
</DL>
</DL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>12:00 pm - 1:30 pm </H3>

<CENTER><P><B>LUNCH AT THE TROJAN CAFETERIA</B></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>1:30 pm - 4:30 pm </H3>

<CENTER><P><B>TOUR OF THE TROJAN NUCLEAR POWER PLANT </B></P></CENTER>

<DL>
<DT>Session Chairman and Coordinator: </DT>

<DD><B>Joseph M. Mihelich</B>, <I>Manager of Engineering, Portland General
Electric Company, Trojan Nuclear Power Plant, Rainier, OR</I> <BR>
Mr. Mihelich will provide an overview of the Trojan project and the areas
to be visited on the plant tour. Areas to be toured include the ISFSI site,
video presentation room, (project video) the containment entry area, and
auxiliary building work areas. Examples of areas that have been decommissioned
will be observed.</DD>

<P>This half day session will be devoted to the actual tour of Trojan and
to the Technology Fair. Several of the presenters from the Monday and Wednesday
sessions, as well as members of the Trojan staff will be available to discuss
issues and programs. Busses will depart Trojan at 4:30 PM for the return
trip to the hotel. </P>
</DL>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>7:00 pm </H3>

<CENTER><P><B>EVENING BANQUET </B></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><B>Harold B. Ray</B>, <I>Southern California Edison Company,
Rosemead, CA<BR>
</I>Mr. Ray will discuss the import of deregulation in long-term decommissioning
strategic planning. </P></CENTER>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

