<html><head><title>Nuke News, 4/4/96</title></head>

<body background="/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif">
<center>
<h1>Nuke News for 4/4/96</h1>
<h3>distributed by Charles Sayles</h3>
<a href="96.04.03.html">Previous Nuke News</a>
<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>

<table width=600>
<tr>
<td>

... An op-ed on nuclear power by Stanford Levin, a professor of
economics at Southern Illinois University and former commissioner of
the Illinois Commerce Commission, appears in this morning's JOURNAL OF
COMMERCE.  The essay, published first in the ST. LOUIS POST-DISPATCH
on 4/1 and reported by this service yesterday, argues "nuclear power
will be one of the least expensive sources of electricity" in the
competitive power market of the future.  A performance-based
regulatory system, as opposed to the current "prescriptive" approach,
would do even more to reduce costs, Levin writes (JOURNAL OF COMMERCE,
4/4/96, p. 6A).

</td>
</tr>
