<html><head><title>Nuke News, 27/3/96</title></head>

<body background="/graphics/gifs/logo.bkgrnd.gif">
<center>
<h1>Nuke News for 27/3/96</h1>
<h3>distributed by Charles Sayles</h3>
<a href="96.03.26.html">Previous Nuke News</a>
<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>

<table width=600>
<tr>
<td>

<i><b>"Plan for Prairie Island Plant Draws Criticism"</b><br>
MINNEAPOLIS STAR-TRIBUNE, 3/23/96</i><br>
Robert Whereatt
<p>

A proposal to put $8 million in state money into a compensation fund
for the Indian tribe living adjacent to Northern States Power Co.'s
Prairie Island nuclear plant was questioned last week by Minnesota
lawmakers.
<p>

Under a previously reached agreement, NSP would contribute $2 million,
and local governments in Goodhue County would transfer some Prairie
Island tax revenues, to the Mdewankton Sioux tribe.  In return, NSP
could drop its search for an off- site repository for 17 casks of
nuclear wastes.  But the latest plan, sponsored by State Sen.  Steven
Novak (D), calls for $8 million from the state treasury as well.
<p>

The tribe says the money would compensate some members who want to
move away from the site.  But members of the state Senate Environment
and Natural Resources Committee called the plan "ransom" and
questioned why NSP is not being asked to chip in more.  In response to
concerns from some that land and money in the compensation package
would be used to build a new casino, a tribal spokesman denied that
was being considered.
<p>

With only a few days left in the legislative session, "and with the
governor opposing a state appropriation," observers on both sides were
not optimistic the latest proposal would be passed.

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>


... China will build four nuclear power plants in its "booming" 
coastal areas by the year 2000, an industry official announced 
yesterday.  China's installed nuclear capacity will account for as 
much as 50f its total electricity supply by 2010, he said (WALL 
STREET JOURNAL, 3/27/96, p. A19, Dow Jones News Service).


</td>
</tr>
