cover, June 96" align="right" width=295>
<center><h3>FEATURE ARTICLES</h3></center>
<dl>
  <dt> <b>ALARA: Two court decisions with dramatically different  
       implications</b>
  <dd> <i>by David Wiedis and Donald E. Jose</i>, p. 30

  <dt> <b>The sodium leak at Monju in perspective</b>
  <dd> <i>by John Lambert</i>, p. 38
</dl>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif" width=300 height=3>
<p>
<center><h3>POWER</h3></center>

Customer choice test is running well for IP. Plaintiffs can sue GPU
for punitive damages. NRC approves Trojan decom plan. Focus on
Finance. Brief shutdown at Oyster Creek. Palo Verde-1 pump repair;
Unit 2 restart; neutrino experiment. TVA gathers comments for
fossil-fueled Bellefonte. NRC denies Thermo-Lag petitions, <b>page
21</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif" width=300 height=3>
