Probabilistic Safety Assessment, September 29-9October 3, 1996 in Park
City, Utah.), <b>page 27</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>
<center><h3>INTERNATIONAL</h3></center>

First reprocessing waste returned to Germany amid protests. Candu
reactors could burn Russian plutonium. Spent fuel rod canning begins
at Yongbyon, North Korea. Chernobyl-1 close set for end of year; fire
near Chernobyl; Unit 3 incident; Chernobyl genetic changes. Nuclear
power contributions in 1995. Cherbov new chairman of Goskomatom. Court
fines BNFL. The sodium leak at Monju in perspective. <b>page 34</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>
