Alpha-emitting bullet targets leukemia cells. DOE issues final EIS for
isotope production. Fission made diamonds in billion-year
coal. Deuterated spider silk reveals crystal structure. <b>page 47</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>
<center><h3>WASTE MANAGEMENT</h3></center>

DOE site cleanup to proceed at a faster pace. UC Berkeley team
analyzes Yucca Mountain criticality scenario. Weapons cleanup
contracts; waste retrieval at Berkeley. (See also the Meeting
Notice/Call for Papers on p. 75 for the Embedded Topical Meeting on
DD&amp;R: Worldwide Experience--DDR, What Does It Mean, November
15-20, 1996, in Washington, D.C.) <b>page 49</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
<p>
<center><h3>INDUSTRY</h3></center>

Entergy makes plans to market nuclear expertise. New companies, new
divisions, acquisitions, pacts, and other business activities. News
about contracts. <b>page 52</b>

<p>
<img src="/graphics/gifs/stripe.gif">
